Don't have non-renewable resources
	make the lairs renew

Change d_breed to not allow i1 == i2 && man_item(i1)

inner locs should be randomly numbered

Multiple starting cities:  because you didn't last time.

Pick a larger numbering space for structures
Put a maximum on HOSTILE, NEUTRAL, etc.
Put a maximum on the # of orders a faction will execute.

Separate PRESS command for regular announcements.

Hades and Faery destroy the idea of a frontier, and subvert gatemastery.


New
---
	fullname		XX
	start <city>
	regen <id> ["name"]

	giveup/create
	create "name"

> P.S.: How is the improved SEEK stuff coming along?  I started thinking
> about syntax and decided that SEEK <days> [<who>] should work okay.


Characters that regen in starting cities should appear in random order.
Turn delay between death and regen?


One way to give more variety would be to have the skills you can pick up
from cities be more geographically skewed.  So if you wanted to learn
Necromancy, you could only do it on a certain island.  If you wanted to
learn about Weather Magic, you would have to have a noble half-way around
the world.  This would make gathering all these skills a more challenging task
and would spread factions out a bit, so that a landowner spending all his
noble-days developing his kingdom wouldn't pick up all the skills so quickly.

Should really fix trade somehow.

   >Other things in Olympia need to be changed to allow greater personal
   >growth of "heroic" nobles, but this would be a start.
   
   Yes.  I've suggested that Rich implement *and enforce* space limits on
   internal locations such as hills and graveyards and such.  That way, a
   noble and a large army couldn't enter, only a small band of nobles and
   maybe some fighting men.  This would let Rich better tune monsters to
   require certain types of forces to defeat.

That I completely agree with.  This is both a real problem and the
correct solution.

"Do it."

>    it would be neat if attacking after the first day of
>    travel out of a province worked only if the attacker matched
>    movement directions with the attackee (this could be
>    implemented with a new parameter on ATTACK giving the movement
>    direction - and if the attacker guessed wrong, he'd still have
>    to move)

> 3. I would like to see more options in combat along the lines of
>    Oly I's [kill|capture|booty] choices, and (ideally) some means
>    of supporting robbery, whereby a player could offer to exchange
>    all booty in exchange for preventing combat.

> ps.  Oh, and idea I had:  I think that nobles that die and are ressurected
> should have their attack & defense lowered by like 10 each.  If defense
> would be lower than 0, no ressurection is possible.  This way there
> would be a slow degeneration of the noble as they are continually raised.
> This would also made the DEFENSE skill a little more attractive.....

Must
----

0.  Add secret selling skill.  Should be very easy to add.

1.  Add a new skill to catch beasts in the wilderness.
    It is similar to wild horse catching.

2.  Players may choose from 6-12 cities to start in.

3.  Get rid of o/0 l/1 in ID's.
	Done in engine, what about mapgen?

4.  Design new map for G2

5.  Don't have subloc npc's auto-attack people who enter.

7.  Remove all forms of NP transfer.  Give each player 6 characters from the
    start.  If a character dies, reincarnate it in its starting location.

	a. potion of slavery goes away		XX
	b. form/bribe/honor/oath/terrorize go away	XX
		loyalty desertions		..
		np's at start			XX
		loyalty report			XX
		np accretion			XX
		np report at top		XX
		nps on skills			XX
		curse noncreate loyalty 9113	XX
	c. persuade oathbound noble goes away	XX
	d. rescued npc prisoners		XX

	e. start player with five units
	f. give player a new unit if one dies
	g. give player a command to give up a character
	h. new way to work to get more units (max 9)


3.  ATTACK always takes three days, regardless of whether the target is
    present and engaged or not.  (except for "meta-errors"; see source)

	[or should all commands take their stated amount of time?
	no, too big a change]


Holding fighters idea needs attention to summoned entities, mobs, etc.
Or wait -- is an army stack a stack, or a unit?

Perhaps require Persuasion for RECRUIT.

Perhaps disallow mages to RECRUIT, due to public revulsion.

Maybe?
------

2.  Make all attacks take three days, regardless of success/failure
    (i.e. ATTACK takes 3 days prep even if the target isn't found).

3.  Non-combat stacks that are smaller than a force trying to
    attack them have a 50% chance to evade the agressor.

4.  Flag armies as ", army".  Perhaps require combat (Military leadership)
    to hold military units.


Combat
------

1.  The combat ratings for peasants, sailors and workers is removed.
2.  Only one who has studied Combat may hold fighters.
3.  Only one who has studied Combat may issue ATTACK.
4.  ATTACK always takes 3 days, regardless of whether the target is found.
5.  ATTACK against a non-Combat unit has a 50% chance of failure.
6.  Monsters don't randomly attack travelers.

#4 doesn't work with hostile  (or does it?)

Alt #5:
	Attack against non-combat unit has 20% chance of succeeding in a
	city or province, 50% in a sublocation.

Make it so that subloc npc's aren't hostile

7.  Change to combat system: alternate sides, 4-in-a-row?


How to make defense easier?
	bigger defensive bonus to towers
	extra bonus for defending...
		a skill?
		if you're at home or something?
	forest defense
		bonus if not an attacker and you're at large in the forest
	mountain defense
	plains defense
	swamp defense
	desert defense


POV growth
----------

Players start with five nobles

Each additional noble requires the following investment of time
into SOLICIT.  SOLICIT may only be used by a noble once per month:
SOLICIT/HIRE/ATTRACT.

	noble 	weeks		rl months	components
	-----	-----		---------	----------
	 6th	  20		    1		    5*4
	 7th	  48		    2		    6*8
	 8th	  56	 	    2		    7*8
	 9th	  96		    3		    8*12
	10th	 144		    4		    9*16
	11th	 200		    5		   10*20
	12th	 264		    6		   11*24

