> 3.  New combat round algorithm is as follows:

I'll have to think about this.  Has anyone else seen it?

> 1.  Capture beasts in battle is removed.

So no one will ever have any beasts?  Then why have rules for
controlling them?

> Inventory may not be removed from garrisons.

I sort of like the ability to use garrisons to store stuff.  What's
wrong with that?

What happens to the inventory when you UNGARRISON?

> Stacks with large numbers of men relative to the number of nobles
> travel slower.

Another thing to ponder.  Does this apply to FLY as well?

> 2.  Up to 5 horses may be caught per month in plains.
>     Chance per day to catch is 50%, up from 25%.
>     Train wild horse to riding horse takes 3 days.
>     Train wild horse to warmount takes 7 days.

This is better although I think warmount is still too hard.  But maybe
with the limitations on number of men they will get built.

> 4.  Summoned entities, such as angry mobs, may not be given anything.

Now there's something I never found a use for.

> 7.  Ocean-land routes take normal time to cross, not one day.

I'm going to miss the coastal routes.  I sort of liked those.  Maybe
have coastal waters (adjacent to land), and deep ocean, and make travel
faster through the former?  It's nice because it makes it more likely to
run into people.

                                        David desJardins

From whalen@stromboli.usc.edu  Thu Mar  9 15:52:10 1995
Received: (from smtp@localhost) by blekko.pbm.com
	id PAA14367 for <skrenta@pbm.com>; Thu, 9 Mar 1995 15:52:09 -0500
Received: from usc.edu(128.125.253.136) by blekko.pbm.com via smtp (V1.3)
	id sma014365; Thu Mar  9 15:52:05 1995
