	id AA16853; Thu, 9 Mar 95 12:54:43 PST
Received: (whalen@localhost)
	by stromboli.usc.edu (8.6.10/8.6.7+ucs)
	id MAA02758 for skrenta@pbm.com; Thu, 9 Mar 1995 12:54:40 -0800
Date: Thu, 9 Mar 1995 12:54:40 -0800
From: Tim Whalen <whalen@stromboli.usc.edu>
Message-Id: <199503092054.MAA02758@stromboli.usc.edu>
To: skrenta@pbm.com
Subject: Garrison problem redux
Status: RO


Last turn I mentioned that a garrison with troops having
a total maintenance of 272 gold in a wilderness province
didn't suffer any attrition.  That, I thought, was an
obvious bug.  This turn I attacked the garrison and it
had 252 gold that I captured!  I just don't believe that
Ergonal put his gold in a garrison for safe keeping.
There is something very wrong going on here and it may
well be that some players have been abusing this bug
for fun and profit.  Viliz has apparently garrisonned
300+ troops in a civ-1 province this turn ([by10]).
Since you can TAKE stuff from garrisons in zero time
UNGARRISON may be a useless command.  I don't know,
maybe the empty garrison stays around until the end
of the turn...  If you garrisonned on the last day
of the month and then took everything from the garrison
at the start of the next month, you may never be at
risk from a surprise attack and never have to spend
any money!  Anyhow, I think there's a problem...

The Survive Fatal Wound was demonstrated as an essentially
useless skill this turn.  I was able to kill Ergonal no
problem.  He escaped the first time, as you mentioned but
was easily killed the following turn.  I can't think of
many situations where the skill would actually help.  I
think you may want to change the mechanics so that the
noble is moved to the nearest GY alive or back to IC
alive.  Those changes are probably going too far though.
It's certainly not worth an NP IMO though.

Tim

From gl8f@fermi.clas.virginia.edu  Thu Mar 16 13:25:49 1995
