From pbm.com!news.uni-stuttgart.de!news.belwue.de!scsing.switch.ch!swidir.switch.ch!newsfeed.ACO.net!Austria.EU.net!EU.net!newsfeed.internetmci.com!news.sprintlink.net!simtel!news.kei.com!eff!news.umbc.edu!nobody 7 Oct 1995 12:42:40 -0400
Path: pbm.com!news.uni-stuttgart.de!news.belwue.de!scsing.switch.ch!swidir.switch.ch!newsfeed.ACO.net!Austria.EU.net!EU.net!newsfeed.internetmci.com!news.sprintlink.net!simtel!news.kei.com!eff!news.umbc.edu!nobody
From: schott@cs.umbc.edu (Brian Schott)
Newsgroups: rec.games.pbm
Subject: Re: oly combat simple fix
Date: 7 Oct 1995 12:42:40 -0400
Organization: University of Maryland, Baltimore County
Lines: 39
Message-ID: <456am0INN4fr@retriever.cs.umbc.edu>
References: <44775c$8ev@saba.info.ucla.edu> <451a53$cvo@saba.info.ucla.edu> <453igk$et@wahoo.ccr-p.ida.org> <454ek4$pel@kaiwan009.kaiwan.com>
NNTP-Posting-Host: retriever.cs.umbc.edu
NNTP-Posting-User: schott

I assume you have tongue in cheek?  Let's do the math shall we?  A
noble starts at (80,80,0).  It takes 6 days to raise 1 point (I assume
once you are grand master the skill only takes 6 days).  So (1250 -
80) * 6 / 30 = 234.  So to get from 80,80,0 to 1250,80,0 would take
234 turns.  If you are willing to wait 4.5 years of REAL TIME, you
*might* survive combat with a novice and 10 peasants.  

I just realized I made a glaring error in my computation, you listed
(1250,1250,0), so that's 9 years of real time, not 4.5.  Of course, if
you are able to find a few magic items, you might be able to shave a
few years off of your effort.

I guess this proves how useful defense and swordplay are.  

These skills might be more valuable (and magic items to boot) if they
provided a bonus to the entire stack.  Every 10 points of defense over
80 adds 1 point of defense to everybody in the stack.  Every 10 points
of archery over 80 adds 1 point to every unit with a missle attack,
etc.

Brian

In article <454ek4$pel@kaiwan009.kaiwan.com>,
Robert Christopher Butchko <rcb@kaiwan009.kaiwan.com> wrote:
>Hmm, is this true? 
>5000 battles fought in 4 seconds, 1250.00 battles/s 
>ATTACKER (Fighting to the death) : 
>    1 noble (80,80,0) [0.50], with: 
>      10 peasants (1,1,0) [2.84]
>    Average losses : 1 noble
>                     7 peasants 
>DEFENDER (Fighting to the death) : 
>    1 Practised Noble (1250,1250,0) [0.50] 
>      LIKELIHOOD OF WIN 49.86% 
>Guess not.  Let's watch those sloppy errors, shall we?  Well, I suppose 





From pbm.com!news.uni-stuttgart.de!news.belwue.de!scsing.switch.ch!swidir.switch.ch!in2p3.fr!univ-lyon1.fr!oleane!plug.news.pipex.net!pipex!tank.news.pipex.net!pipex!newsfeed.internetmci.com!howland.reston.ans.net!swrinde!elroy.jpl.nasa.gov!news.aero.org!sun-dimas!srt 9 Oct 1995 16:20:55 GMT
