From pbm.com!news.uni-stuttgart.de!news.belwue.de!scsing.switch.ch!swidir.switch.ch!newsfeed.ACO.net!Austria.EU.net!EU.net!howland.reston.ans.net!newsfeed.internetmci.com!chi-news.cic.net!news.uoregon.edu!waikato!comp.vuw.ac.nz!bill 12 Oct 1995 04:39:55 GMT
Path: pbm.com!news.uni-stuttgart.de!news.belwue.de!scsing.switch.ch!swidir.switch.ch!newsfeed.ACO.net!Austria.EU.net!EU.net!howland.reston.ans.net!newsfeed.internetmci.com!chi-news.cic.net!news.uoregon.edu!waikato!comp.vuw.ac.nz!bill
From: bill@rses.vuw.ac.nz (Bill Viggers)
Newsgroups: rec.games.pbm
Subject: Re: Oly: changes in G2- generalship skill
Date: 12 Oct 1995 04:39:55 GMT
Organization: Research School of Earth Sciences, Victoria University of Wellington, New Zealand.
Lines: 42
Distribution: world
Message-ID: <45i66r$959@st-james.comp.vuw.ac.nz>
References: <44ucs2$9ea@news.aero.org>  <450n2o$43h@blekko.pbm.com> <DG1urw.5Jz@isltd.insignia.com> <krause.83.00081DDF@wifak.uni-wuerzburg.de>
NNTP-Posting-Host: dope.geog.vuw.ac.nz

In article <krause.83.00081DDF@wifak.uni-wuerzburg.de>, krause@wifak.uni-wuerzburg.de (Guenter Krause) writes:
|> Here are my 2 cents about improving(?) the combat system
|> 
|> How about introducing a new skill, generalship, under combat, perhaps costing 
|> a noble point.
|> 

	Way back in the days of Oly-1 (and no, thats not the play test of Oly-II)
	there was a skill called Military Leadership.  Basically the side that had a
	better leader got a combat bonus.

[Heh, looking round I even managed to dig up the old lore sheets for it :-]


|> It could have levels (studied weeks or some function thereof) which allow a 
|> certain  number of men/beasts to be commanded by a noble

	I like the idea of levels, but I'd prefer to see it use the current
	experience system.  You become a better leader by leading armies in
	battle.  I like this for two reasons.
	1: it reuses the experience system (which is under used but good)
and 	2: it means that in order to get better a noble is going to have to
		do something that puts them at a little risk.  

	The combination of 1&2 will also mean that attaining high levels of
	skill in Military leadership should be harder to get.

	Actually I think that high skill levels should be harder to get than
	they are at the moment.  Someone can go from not knowing a skill to
	becoming a grand master in just over a year of _casual_ use of a 
	skill.  Doubling the amount of required months of use would be a start.
	(okay, okay I'm off topic).


	As to the effect of such a skill, well, I'm easy.  Your army size
	limit is fine, as was the original bonus to combat.  Another 	
	alternative could be an 'army quality limit'.  Basically you don't
	need very much skill to lead a bunch of peasants, but if you want to
	be able to make full use of your elite guards then you had better
	be a good general.	

Bill.

Basil A. Daust:
	show aura left in appear common, etc.
	fix dragon weight
From pbm.com!news.uni-stuttgart.de!news.belwue.de!fu-berlin.de!cs.tu-berlin.de!informatik.uni-bremen.de!nordwest.pop.de!news.hamburg.pop.de!news.gun.de!msn!noris.net!xlink.net!howland.reston.ans.net!newsfeed.internetmci.com!tank.news.pipex.net!pipex!dish.news.pipex.net!pipex!lade.news.pipex.net!pipex!insignia!Jeremy.Maiden Sun, 15 Oct 1995 20:17:29 GMT
Newsgroups: rec.games.pbm
Path: pbm.com!news.uni-stuttgart.de!news.belwue.de!fu-berlin.de!cs.tu-berlin.de!informatik.uni-bremen.de!nordwest.pop.de!news.hamburg.pop.de!news.gun.de!msn!noris.net!xlink.net!howland.reston.ans.net!newsfeed.internetmci.com!tank.news.pipex.net!pipex!dish.news.pipex.net!pipex!lade.news.pipex.net!pipex!insignia!Jeremy.Maiden
From: jeremy@insignia.com (Jeremy Maiden)
Subject: Oly: Fixing beastmastery in G1
Message-ID: <DGIB16.K1E@isltd.insignia.com>
X-Posted-From: InterNews 1.0@sacrum.isltd.insignia.com.
Lines: 24
Sender: -Not-Authenticated-[1895]
Nntp-Posting-Host: c1macdyn252.isltd.insignia.com
Organization: Insignia Solutions plc
Date: Sun, 15 Oct 1995 20:17:29 GMT
Xdisclaimer: No attempt was made to authenticate the sender's name.

Following a general view that beastmastery is too good, there've
been several suggested changes to bring it into balance with the
rest of the game. Most of the proposed changes have been more
suitable for a fresh start in G2, here's an "upgrade" path for G1.

1) Use the wild horse/riding horse idea to split each existing
beast type into wild and trained versions - different item numbers.

2) Introduce a skill (or maybe skill per type) of training wild
beasts, taking some time to train each individual creature.

3) Make new beasts captured or bred always the wild type.

4) For a transtional period, have wild and trained beasts both
function as the original single type.

5) On some future pre-announced turn stop the wild versions
having any combat value when held by players.

Suitable choices of all the numbers could give a toned down but
still valuble beastmastery skill, but have a relativly small impact
on the existing game.

Jeremy

From pbm.com!news.uni-stuttgart.de!news.belwue.de!fu-berlin.de!simtel!news.sprintlink.net!news.telepac.pt!usenet Sun, 15 Oct 1995 22:07:03 GMT
Path: pbm.com!news.uni-stuttgart.de!news.belwue.de!fu-berlin.de!simtel!news.sprintlink.net!news.telepac.pt!usenet
