In article <463n6o$1i9@news.aero.org> srt@sun-dimas.aero.org (Scott Turner) writes:
>whalen@stromboli.usc.edu (Tim Whalen) writes:
>>C. Rethinking Faerie, Cloudlands and Hades to discourage the "warp zone"
>>   concept.  These should be places that anybody *can* get to but that
>
>The argument here is "there shouldn't exist any powerful thing in the
>game that any particular faction (or group) can control" ---
> ...
> It's no different than any other set of regions in Oly.
>
>					-- Scott T.

No, the point was that an unrestricted "warp zone" is a bad thing to
have in Olympia.  I think that there is an overwhelming group percep-
tion that the time required to move from point A to point B should
be fairly long.  Witness the general concensus that roads would, if
anything, make Olympia worse.  I would like to see flying in G2 a
somewhat rare mode of transport.  I know of factions in G1 that
refuse to walk anywhere, ever.  Gate travel is costly enough that
it's virtually never used.  The three worst offenders to appropriate
travel times are Faerie, flying and Hades.  Okay, okay, I admit that
I'd like to see more public access to cloudlands in g2, but who
really gives a flying stack about cloudlands.



From pbm.com!news.uni-stuttgart.de!news.belwue.de!scsing.switch.ch!swsbe6.switch.ch!swidir.switch.ch!in2p3.fr!oleane!simtel!lll-winken.llnl.gov!ames!waikato!comp.vuw.ac.nz!bill 19 Oct 1995 00:08:53 GMT
Path: pbm.com!news.uni-stuttgart.de!news.belwue.de!scsing.switch.ch!swsbe6.switch.ch!swidir.switch.ch!in2p3.fr!oleane!simtel!lll-winken.llnl.gov!ames!waikato!comp.vuw.ac.nz!bill
From: bill@rses.vuw.ac.nz (Bill Viggers)
Newsgroups: rec.games.pbm
Subject: Re: Olympia and Game Theory (LONG)
Date: 19 Oct 1995 00:08:53 GMT
Organization: Research School of Earth Sciences, Victoria University of Wellington, New Zealand.
Lines: 40
Distribution: world
Message-ID: <4644ul$lpd@st-james.comp.vuw.ac.nz>
